=Ruy Lopez Main Line=

Whenever White opens with 1. e4, her most reliable plan is then to prepare to play d4. There is a very good reason not to play [[/8. d4|8. d4?]] instantly - click and learn.

Instead, it must be prepared with [[/8. c3|8. c3]]. With White's kingside fully developed there is no reason to delay this useful move any longer.

Note that h3 will be a useful move, but not yet - because it turns out that 8. c3 is also necessary to give the b3-bishop a retreat square. A White player who forgets her move order and plays [[/8. h3|8. h3]] is liable to have her bishop confiscated with 8...Na5.

